description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and motivated Band 5 staff nurse to support the cardiac rehabilitation service as a temporary post to support the existing team as part of staff’s maternity leave cover.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking the skills of an experienced staff nurse who would gain experience within the cardiology service who can make a difference to the health and wellbeing of individuals referred to the service&lt;strong&gt;. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will need to demonstrate knowledge of national and local issues and be committed to partnership working with other providers. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As part of a team and working in conjunction with GP’s, mainstream nursing, social and secondary care services, you will be supporting the team to provide a patient focused, co-ordinated case management approach across primary care. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The post holder will participate in and influence efforts across health and social services to support patient choice, improve quality of life, and promote self-management whilst adopting the community care team approach.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Interview date to be confirmed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact Sharon Stockdale Cardiology Team Leader – 03033309605&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sharon.stockdale@locala.org.uk.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
